			<title>RE: This is the time to pay attention to yourself</title>
			<link>https://www.brahmakumaris.org#comment-2019</link>
			<description><![CDATA[Janine:  An important significance of spiritual growth is to realize that each one is an actor playing their individual part on this world stage.  Each actor has to pay attention to his/her own part and to play their part to the best of their ability.  While paying attention to one's own part, it is also a good practice to be a detached observer to the part of others.  This practice of being a detached observer will allow you to be the following:  a.  To separate yourself from what others are doing and not to define yourself through the actions of others. b.   To stay true to your own innate values and not to compromise them while interacting with others. c.   To invest your resources into things that are meaningful with long-lasting impact e.g. your daughter's education without expecting others to do the same. d.    To be the master of who you are and not to become the victim of those around you.  The practice of meditation fills the self with inner strength to do the above.  Hope this helps you to understand the power of practice.]]></description>
